<title>UK: Hall Engineering buys ASW unit.</title>
<headline>Hall Engineering buys ASW unit.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-10-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>British group, Hall Engineering Plc, said on Tuesday it had agreed to buy Cardiff Wire, a unit of ASW Holdings Plc for 5.95 million stg cash.</p>
<p>Of that sum 5.25 million stg will be payable on completion which is expected to take place on November 1.</p>
<p>Cardiff Wire is a maker of steel and wire products for industrial use and had turnover of 20 million stg in 1995, with an operating loss of 1.4 million stg.</p>
